'''Lingua Franca Nova''' (abreviá '''LFN''' i tambe konosi komo '''Elefen''') ta un idioma artifisial, kreá na aña 1965 pa C. George Boeree di e Universidat di Shippensburg na [[Pennsylvania]].<ref>Malawskey, Nick, [https://www.pennlive.com/midstate/2011/11/pennsylvania_dialects.html 
Pennsylvania's dialects are as varied as its downtowns -- and dahntahns], Pennlive.com (29 november 2011). Rekuperá 13 oktober 2021.</ref> E ta basá riba e vocabulario di e idioma [[frances|franses]], [[italiano]], [[português]], [[spaño]] i [[katalan]].<ref>Harrison, Richard H. (2008) ''Lingua Franca Nova.'' '''Invented Languages, 1,''' pp.&nbsp;30 –33.</ref>
Lingua Franca Nova a wordu kreá pa uzo den komunikashon internashonal i tin un [[gramatika]] hopi sensio, meskos ku mayoria di e [[idioma krioyo|idiomanan krioyo]].
